        <div class="exercise">
            
        <div class="problem" id="904ac574-fa1e-ffad-31ee-c965b209770a">Why do passengers get thrown to the side when the car they are driving in goes around a corner?</div>

        <div class="solution"><p>Passengers have inertia and so tend to travel in the same straight line. The car has changed direction and so it feels that the passengers are being thrown, but it is really the car coming towards the passengers.</p></div></div>

